<paragraph blockId="5.[241,1074,1276,1404]" pageId="5" pageNumber="244">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[267,382,1276,1297]" pageId="5" pageNumber="244">Variation.</emphasis>
The 
<specimenCount box="[436,596,1276,1297]" pageId="5" pageNumber="244" type="generic">nine specimens</specimenCount>
examined do not show a significant variation in morphology because they are fundamentally uniform in clypeal and pronotal ornamentation as well as in body size. On the other hand two distinct colour patterns occur in this species: 
<specimenCount box="[559,714,1356,1377]" pageId="5" pageNumber="244" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
(
<specimenCount box="[731,801,1356,1377]" pageId="5" pageNumber="244" type="male">1 male</specimenCount>
and 
<specimenCount box="[852,945,1356,1377]" pageId="5" pageNumber="244" type="female">1 female</specimenCount>
) from Natal are entirely black.
</paragraph>
